                     <a id="a000105"></a>
                     <div class="content" id="entry-105">
                        <h3 class="content">the carrousel</h3>
                        <div class="content">
                           <div class="content">
                              <p><img src="http://drzaius.ics.uci.edu/mt3.14/johannab/archives/carrousel.jpg" width="160" height="230"></p>

<p>i saw this project at ubicomp 2004, but we make money not art recently blogged it so i thought i might as well throw in my 2 cents.  <a href="http://studiolab.io.tudelft.nl/ross/project/">the carrousel</a>, designed by <a href="http://studiolab.io.tudelft.nl/ross/">philip ross</a>, is a tangible interface that allows one to change the ambience of the room [specfically the lighting, music, and video projection].  something about getting to play with the interface myself really sold me on it.  it's very natural feeling, a smooth combination of wood, metal and technology.  also, philip really managed to nail the intuitiveness of use.  the fluidity of "sculpting" the atmosphere really comes across.  bravo.</p>

<p>[thanks <a href="http://www.we-make-money-not-art.com/archives/004656.php">we make money not art</a>]</p>
                              
                              <p class="posted">
                                 <span class="post-footers">roxy said on 01:52 AM</span> <span class="separator">|</span> <a class="permalink" href="http://drzaius.ics.uci.edu/blogs/setbang/2005/02/the_carrousel.html">Permalink</a>
                                 | <a href="http://drzaius.ics.uci.edu/blogs/setbang/2005/02/the_carrousel.html#comments">Comments (0)</a>
                                 
                              </p>
                           </div>
